<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Who are you calling stupid?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Lightning~">Lightning~</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:27 a.m. 27/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Who are you calling stupid?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2232" TARGET=_self>Re: Can anyone confirm these? XP Loss to DOT and pet death?</A> (Stupid)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Or maybe you call yourself that... would be fitting.

<P>Anyway, here is how you lose exp, and like Ellos said, zone and different spells don't matter - ANY DoT will
<BR>cause exp loss upon death. Sometimes I wonder if you people really play Rallos, but then again this board isn't
<BR>for purely Rallos players *shrug*.
<P>Here are some ways to lose exp in PvP:
<P>DoT's (by far the worst and most common)
<BR>Lightning spells (Wizards use these a lot from levels 12-20 {Shock of Lightning and Lightning Bolt})
<BR>Someone's pet killing you
<BR>Having someone beat on you until you are low on life while fighting a mob and then letting the mob get the kill
<BR>Hitting someone until they are unconscious over and over until they finally get down so low they bleed to death
<P>There are probably a couple more out there... but those are by far the most common and should be fixed. The
<BR>unconscious bug can be fixed with specific coding, or at least partially fixed. For example, if another player strikes
<BR>you unconscious to the point where you are going to bleed to death, then bleeding to death should not cause exp loss.
<BR>DoT's are pretty easy to fix, and lightning spells shouldn't even be an issue.
<P>I feel exactly the same Ellos does on this subject. While I have not lost much experience at all do to these bugs,
<BR>I have lost probably a bubble net experience. I just can't believe that this hasn't been fixed in so freakin' long...
<BR>either it is a new problem that sprouted after Beta (highly unlikely), or someone just isn't listening at Verant.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
